HOME_MAIN = r'<main class="hub-home-v21" id="home">\n  <section class="home-hero-v21" aria-label="Indoor Positioning Hub profile hero">\n    <div class="home-hero-bg-v21" aria-hidden="true"></div>\n    <div class="home-hero-grid-v21">\n      <div class="home-hero-copy-v21">\n        <p class="eyebrow-v21">Indoor Positioning Hub</p>\n        <h1>Ahmed Mansour, Ph.D.</h1>\n        <p class="subtitle-v21">Indoor positioning, localization, navigation, and spatial intelligence for smart built environments.</p>\n        <p class="lead-v21">This hub brings together Ahmed Mansour\'s academic profile, publication portfolio, downloadable papers, citation resources, datasets, code links, and visual research maps. The work connects smartphone sensing, Wi-Fi fingerprinting, pedestrian dead reckoning, mobile crowdsensing, autonomous radio mapping, indoor-outdoor awareness, and deployment-ready indoor spatial intelligence.</p>\n        <div class="hero-actions-v21">\n          <a class="btn primary" href="publications.html">Explore publications</a>\n          <a class="btn secondary" href="#research-atlas">Research atlas</a>\n          <a class="btn ghost" href="assets/cv/ahmed-mansour-public-cv.pdf">Download CV</a>\n          <a class="btn ghost" href="citation-resources.html">Citation resources</a>\n        </div>\n        <div class="hero-meta-v21" aria-label="Research keywords">\n          <span>Wi-Fi fingerprinting</span>\n          <span>PDR</span>\n          <span>GNSS/PDR integration</span>\n          <span>Mobile crowdsensing</span>\n          <span>Radio maps</span>\n          <span>Indoor-outdoor awareness</span>\n        </div>\n      </div>\n      <aside class="profile-panel-v21" aria-label="Ahmed Mansour profile card">\n        <div class="profile-photo-shell-v21">\n          <img src="assets/img/profile/ahmed-mansour-photo.webp" alt="Ahmed Mansour academic profile photo" loading="eager" decoding="async">\n        </div>\n        <div class="profile-card-text-v21">\n          <h2>Indoor positioning researcher</h2>\n          <p>Researcher in geomatics, indoor localization, smartphone sensing, crowdsensing-based IPS, PDR, radio-map maintenance, and smart built-environment positioning.</p>\n          <div class="profile-mini-stats-v21">\n            <span><strong>17+</strong> research outputs</span>\n            <span><strong>IPS</strong> methods and deployment</span>\n          </div>\n        </div>\n      </aside>\n    </div>\n  </section>\n\n  <section class="affiliation-strip-v21" aria-label="Affiliations and academic background">\n    <div class="affiliation-card-v21">\n      <img src="assets/home/polyu-logo.webp" alt="The Hong Kong Polytechnic University logo" loading="lazy" decoding="async">\n      <div>\n        <strong>The Hong Kong Polytechnic University</strong>\n        <span>Ph.D. research training and postdoctoral work in geomatics, indoor positioning, sensor fusion, and smart built environments.</span>\n      </div>\n    </div>\n    <div class="affiliation-card-v21">\n      <img src="assets/home/cairo-university-logo.webp" alt="Cairo University logo" loading="lazy" decoding="async">\n      <div>\n        <strong>Cairo University</strong>\n        <span>Civil engineering, public works, geomatics, surveying, and foundational engineering background.</span>\n      </div>\n    </div>\n  </section>\n\n  <section class="home-section-v21 definitions-v21" id="definitions" aria-label="Indoor positioning localization and navigation definitions">\n    <div class="section-heading-v21 centered">\n      <p class="eyebrow-v21">Field guide</p>\n      <h2>What are indoor positioning, indoor localization, and indoor navigation?</h2>\n      <p>These terms are closely related but not identical. The distinction helps readers understand how measurements, estimated locations, and movement guidance become useful services inside buildings where satellite positioning is weak or unavailable.</p>\n    </div>\n    <div class="definition-grid-v21">\n      <article class="definition-card-v21">\n        <span class="definition-icon-v21">📍</span>\n        <h3>Indoor positioning</h3>\n        <p>Indoor positioning estimates the position of a person, smartphone, robot, asset, or sensor inside buildings using radio signals, inertial sensors, maps, vision, magnetic fields, barometers, or combinations of these measurements.</p>\n      </article>\n      <article class="definition-card-v21">\n        <span class="definition-icon-v21">🏢</span>\n        <h3>Indoor localization</h3>\n        <p>Indoor localization determines where the user or object is in an indoor reference frame, such as a coordinate, floor, room, corridor, zone, landmark, or building-level map representation.</p>\n      </article>\n      <article class="definition-card-v21">\n        <span class="definition-icon-v21">🧭</span>\n        <h3>Indoor navigation</h3>\n        <p>Indoor navigation uses position, heading, motion state, route information, and spatial context to guide movement, support wayfinding, enable location-aware services, and connect positioning outputs to decisions.</p>\n      </article>\n    </div>\n  </section>\n\n  <section class="home-section-v21 profile-summary-v21" aria-label="Profile summary">\n    <div class="profile-summary-grid-v21">\n      <div>\n        <p class="eyebrow-v21">Academic profile</p>\n        <h2>From positioning measurements to indoor spatial intelligence</h2>\n        <p>The hub is organized to help readers move from a research question to the relevant paper, method, dataset, figure, or citation entry. The work connects smartphone sensing, radio signals, human mobility, map information, and deployment constraints into practical positioning systems for buildings, campuses, cities, and smart built environments.</p>\n      </div>\n      <div class="profile-focus-list-v21">\n        <span>Seamless indoor-outdoor positioning</span>\n        <span>User-friendly crowd-powered IPS</span>\n        <span>Autonomous 3D radio-map scaling</span>\n        <span>Robust PDR and heading correction</span>\n        <span>GNSS/PDR integration in urban areas</span>\n        <span>Deployment-aware spatial intelligence</span>\n      </div>\n    </div>\n  </section>\n\n  <section class="home-section-v21 research-atlas-v21" id="research-atlas" aria-label="Research themes and visual research atlas">\n    <div class="section-heading-v21 centered">\n      <p class="eyebrow-v21">Research Themes and Visual Research Atlas</p>\n      <h2>A thematic map of Ahmed Mansour\'s work across indoor positioning research, engineering, and deployment.</h2>\n      <p>The atlas links core papers, system concepts, and visual explanations across sensing, inference, mapping, crowdsensing, pedestrian navigation, and deployment readiness.</p>\n    </div>\n    <div class="atlas-grid-v21">\n      <article class="atlas-card-v21 atlas-wide-v21">\n        <img src="assets/home/indoor-navigation-office.webp" alt="Indoor navigation and positioning in a smart building" loading="lazy" decoding="async">\n        <div class="atlas-card-body-v21">\n          <h3>Smart indoor positioning in real buildings</h3>\n          <p>Indoor positioning systems must work in complex spaces with changing signals, moving users, multiple floors, and limited user attention. This direction connects research outputs to operational indoor services.</p>\n          <a href="publications.html">Open publication portfolio</a>\n        </div>\n      </article>\n      <article class="atlas-card-v21">\n        <img src="assets/home/layered-building-positioning.webp" alt="Layered indoor positioning and localization concept" loading="lazy" decoding="async">\n        <div class="atlas-card-body-v21">\n          <h3>Signals, sensors, maps, and context</h3>\n          <p>Research themes include Wi-Fi fingerprinting, PDR, sensor fusion, indoor-outdoor detection, radio-map maintenance, and context-aware positioning pipelines.</p>\n          <a href="research-themes.html">Explore research themes</a>\n        </div>\n      </article>\n      <article class="atlas-card-v21 atlas-text-card-v21">\n        <h3>Core directions</h3>\n        <ul>\n          <li>Indoor positioning and localization</li>\n          <li>Wi-Fi fingerprinting and autonomous radio maps</li>\n          <li>Pedestrian dead reckoning and heading control</li>\n          <li>Mobile crowdsensing and user-centered IPS</li>\n          <li>Indoor-outdoor awareness and seamless positioning</li>\n          <li>Spatial intelligence for smart built environments</li>\n        </ul>\n      </article>\n    </div>\n  </section>\n\n  <section class="home-section-v21 publication-entry-v21" aria-label="Publication and citation access">\n    <div class="section-heading-v21">\n      <p class="eyebrow-v21">Publication access</p>\n      <h2>Find papers, PDFs, citation records, and visual explanations</h2>\n      <p>Each publication page is designed for fast reading and reuse: first-page preview, PDF access where available, DOI metadata, BibTeX, when-to-cite guidance, long research-story summary, and selected visual explanations.</p>\n    </div>\n    <div class="entry-grid-v21">\n      <a href="publications.html"><strong>Publication portfolio</strong><span>Visual paper cards with first-page previews, DOI links, venues, and topic cues.</span></a>\n      <a href="citation-resources.html"><strong>Citation resources</strong><span>BibTeX entries, citation-ready paper titles, and paper-use guidance.</span></a>\n      <a href="resources.html"><strong>Datasets and code</strong><span>Shared resources, reproducibility links, and supporting research materials.</span></a>\n      <a href="about.html"><strong>About Ahmed Mansour</strong><span>Academic background, research focus, and contact links.</span></a>\n    </div>\n  </section>\n</main>'

